Just finished an episode of "The Daily AI Brief" /podcasts and came across an interesting take on how companies will (or won’t) leverage AI for success. TL;DListened 👇

🔎 Phase 0: Exploration
Companies begin experimenting with AI running pilots, identifying use cases, and exploring scalability.

🤑 Phase 1: Cost Reduction
AI becomes a tool for efficiency helping businesses deliver the same just faster and at a lower cost.

💡 Phase 2: Innovation & Expansion
Often running parallel to Phase 1, this is when businesses realise they can leverage AI to innovate and expand capabilities. AI moves from 
efficiency to innovation.

💥Phase 3: Growth & Flourishing
Only some companies will reach this stage, fully embracing AI as a creation tool. Those that do will gain an innovative advantage innovating faster, adapting more quickly and delivering offerings their competitors can’t match.

The real question for me is how quickly companies will adapt before AI shifts the competitive landscape completely.

- Crypto: Available 24/7, anywhere in the world

When you use @togethercrew’s AI bot (available in Discord), this is what’s happening in the background:

1. We take your prompt
2. We split your prompt apart and give each sub-prompt to an agent
3. Each agent will go and look for answers
4. We’ll paste the answers together, turn it into a coherent sentence and answer your question
